    <body.content>
      <block class="lead_paragraph">
        <p>For the first time since it began to reduce its diamond stockpile in a strategic shift, De Beers, the world's biggest diamond company, signaled publicly that it wanted talks with the United States Justice Department to lift a ban on trading in the United States. Antitrust regulators in the United States have accused De Beers of using its hold on the diamond trade to fix prices.</p>
        <p>Alan Cowell (NYT)</p>
